From: PS4 Linux Baikal Port <noreply@ps4-linux>
Subject: [PATCH] amdgpu: v20 - skip DP link training for Liverpool/Gladius

After v19 made ICC mailbox commands work via polling, the next blocker
for HDMI display became:

  [drm:amdgpu_atombios_dp_link_train] *ERROR* clock recovery tried 5 times
  [drm:amdgpu_atombios_dp_link_train] *ERROR* clock recovery failed

amdgpu's standard DP clock-recovery loop never converges on PS4
hardware.  The reason: the "DP link" between the Liverpool GPU and the
Panasonic MN864729/MN86471A internal HDMI bridge chip isn't a real
external DP connection.  It's a fixed-mode internal link that the
bridge chip programs itself during its enable sequence
(ps4_bridge_pre_enable / ps4_bridge_enable).  The bridge does NOT
respond to kernel-driven DPCD-based clock-recovery requests, so the
training loop times out after 5 voltage-swing retries and amdgpu
bails out of the modeset before bridge_enable ever runs.

Fix: skip kernel-side DP link training when adev->asic_type is
CHIP_LIVERPOOL or CHIP_GLADIUS.  The bridge's enable callback is what
actually programs the link.  Without this, the call chain is:

  encoder_atomic_enable
    setup_dig_transmitter(ENABLE)
    amdgpu_atombios_dp_link_train  ← fails 5x, bails out
    setup_dig_encoder(DP_VIDEO_ON)  ← never reached

With this:

  encoder_atomic_enable
    setup_dig_transmitter(ENABLE)
    amdgpu_atombios_dp_link_train  ← early return for Liverpool
    setup_dig_encoder(DP_VIDEO_ON)
  bridge_pre_enable                ← finally runs
  bridge_enable                    ← finally runs, programs MN864729

Builds on 0001 (which added Liverpool/Gladius to dp_get_dp_link_config
forcing min_lane_num=4) but takes the surgical approach of bypassing
training entirely rather than trying to make it succeed.

If v20 works:
- bridge_pre_enable / bridge_enable run
- HDMI bridge gets programmed
- Monitor shows console output

---
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/atombios_dp.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/atombios_dp.c
@@ -736,6 +736,15 @@
 	struct amdgpu_atombios_dp_link_train_info dp_info;
 	u8 tmp;
 
+	/* PS4 Liverpool/Gladius: the internal DP link goes from the GPU to a
+	 * Panasonic MN864729/MN86471A bridge chip that handles training
+	 * itself.  Kernel-side DP link training never completes clock
+	 * recovery on this hardware (5x retries → fail), and the bridge's
+	 * pre_enable/enable callbacks are what actually program the link.
+	 * Skip kernel link training so amdgpu modeset can proceed. */
+	if (adev->asic_type == CHIP_LIVERPOOL || adev->asic_type == CHIP_GLADIUS)
+		return;
+
 	if (!amdgpu_encoder->enc_priv)
 		return;
 
